translated:
Carl Wallis, clergyman, Gränna, born on April 12, 1904 in Jönköping, son of wholesaler Carl W. and Emilia Dahlström. Married in 1932 to Carola Allgulin. Children: Elisabeth, born on March 16. Completed his studies at Jönköping in 1923, graduated with a Bachelor of Arts in 1924, Bachelor of Theology and practical theological examination in 1928, ordained as a priest in the Växjö diocese in 1929. Served as curate in Långaryd, assistant pastor in Skirö and curate in Vallsjö. Became curate in Bredaryd in 1930 and pastor in Gränna since 1942. Chairman of the church council, vice chairman of the National Elementary School Board, chairman and director of the lecture association, leader of the Gränna Scout Corps, district chaplain in the northern Småland scout district. Published works include "Det stora valet" (installation sermon in 1942) and newspaper articles. 
John Wilhelm Victor Car-lén-, captain, gymnastics director, Gothenburg, born on July 16, 1883 in Hjo, son of Captain Gustaf W. and Maria Carlén. Married from 1913 to 1921 and from 1925 to 1928 to Eira Hörnfeldt; married for the second time in 1937 to gymnastics director Marianne Carlberg. Children: Gull Brita, born in 1914, married to Gunnar Bäcker-Backlund, Ulla Marianne, born in 1918, married to editor Bengt Grafström. Completed his studies in Skara in 1902, graduated as a gymnastics director from GCI in 1909. Lieutenant in the Västgöta Regiment from 1904, promoted to lieutenant in 1910, captain in 1917. Worked as a physiotherapist in London from 1909 to 1910, gymnastics teacher in Enköping and physiotherapist under Dr. Westerlund from 1910 to 1911. Gymnastics teacher at Malmö Högskola from 1912 to 1947, also served as inspector of physical education in Malmö elementary schools from 1915 to 1943. Honorary chairman of Malmö gymnastics and fencing club, Malmö gymnastics association, Swedish gymnastics teachers' society southern district, and Skaradjäknarna southern district. Honorary member of the Danish gymnastics association and Skåne gymnastics association. Member of the central board of the Swedish gymnastics teachers' society, vice chairman since 1928, member of the board of the Swedish gymnastics association since 1916. Led several international gymnastics trips as a representative of Sweden, member of the Swedish gymnastics mass troop at the Lingiad in Stockholm in 1939, chairman of the special committee for Lingiad in 1949. Published works include "Dagövningar för folkskolor" (1934), "Utvalda lekar" (1936), "Hemgymn. gör underverk" (co-authored with Alvar Medin in 1941), "Det mesta är sant" (1945), and "Mera nästan sant" (1946), in addition to numerous articles in newspapers and magazines. Speaker. Awarded with the Order of the North Star, Order of Vasa, ProPatria Gold Medal, Ling Anniversary Medal, Riksidrottsmärket (the Swedish National Sports Badge), Ling Medal, Honorary Medal of the Nordic Gymnastics Association, and various Swedish and international awards.
